{"key":"processedPost-19967165","value":{"id":19967165,"first":19960917,"last":20008539,"when":1399740018,"utime":"05/10/14 07:40 PM","content":"The bottom line is you can fruit in open air if you mist enough.&nbsp; However, none of us have time for that so we use terrariums to hold in some moisture.&nbsp; However, if we hold in too much, we impede fresh air exchange.&nbsp; This is the tightrope a shotgun terrarium is designed to walk. <br />A bit of extra verm on top gives you a place to store some water for the cakes when you're going to be gone for a day or two.<br />Be careful not to saturate your cakes or let them dry out.&nbsp; That's the balancing act we as cultivators must learn, and it only comes with experience.&nbsp; Every one of us either has or will fuck up a few grows until we get it down.<br />RR","title":"Re: Questions on SGFC Conditions"}}